verbose_text: In patients who had received pretreatment with OACs, baseline levels of F1.2, D-dimer and TAT were lower than in patients who were untreated or naive to OACs (F1.2 : 87.23 vs. 214.99 pmol/L, p < 0.001; D-dimer : 0.20 vs. 0.40 mg/L FEU, p < 0.001; and TAT : 4.48 vs. 5.71 ug/L, p = 0.003).
evidence: levels of F1.2, D-dimer and TAT
